China Closes 426 Dairy Firms After Inspection, China Daily Says

-- B y   W e n d y   L e u n g
-- 
2011-04-03T04:16:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/china-closes-426-dairy-firms-after-inspection-china-daily-says.html
China will shut down 426 dairy
producers after a quality inspection,  China Daily  reported,
citing the General Administration of Quality Supervision,
Inspection and Quarantine spokesman Li Yuanping.  Another 107 firms will have to halt operations until they
carry out improvements, China Daily said. Over half of the
producers are authorized to continue operations, it said.  A total of 643 companies passed the review conducted among
1,176 dairy product makers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Leung in  Hong Kong  at 
 wleung12@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Tighe at 
 ptighe@bloomberg.net  